HEADWORD: Locum tenens
<hw>Lo"cum te"nens</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., holding
the place; <ets>locus</ets> place + <ets>tenens</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>tenere</ets> to hold. Cf. <er>Lieutenant</er>.]</ety> <def>A
substitute or deputy; one filling an office for a time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Locus</ent>⟦br⟧
